<refsect1>
<title>Using BTK+ on DirectFB</title>

<para>
The DirectFB port of BTK+ is an implementation of BDK (and therefore BTK+) 
on top of the <ulink url="http://www.directfb.org">DirectFB</ulink> 
libraries.
</para>

<para>
Like the obsolete linux-fb port of BTK+, it runs on the Linux framebuffer,
but the DirectFB libraries provide additional features like hardware graphics 
acceleration, input device handling and abstraction and an integrated windowing 
system.
</para>

<refsect2><title>Build requirements</title>

<para>
Beyond the usual BTK+ build requirements, the DirectFB backend (obviously) 
needs the DirectFB libraries (at least 0.9.21) and bairo compiled with 
DirectFB support.
</para>
</refsect2>
